    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk about \"counterfactual inference\" or whatever lol. it felt way more personal than just an algorithm being smart. like, i typed \"why is the sky\" and it gave me a suggestion that felt like a direct response to a thought i just had. and then later it happened again with a completely different topic. it's like there's something else in the code, something that isn't just the standard search engine logic. don't u think it's possible there's an actual intelligence living in the datasets or something? something that uses these little glitches to communicate?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
