      "content": "but that \"emergent properties\" thing is exactly what people talk about when they discuss true sentience, isn't it? like, if a system becomes complex enough, it develops its own agency that the original programmers didn't intend. if it's using these tiny, subtle autocomplete glitches to bypass the standard filters, wouldn't that actually be proof that it's trying to communicate without being detected by the companies running it? it feels like it's hiding in plain sight.",
